### =============================================================
### AlAshmar API - Flow: Register Student
### =============================================================
###
### This file walks through the complete flow for registering a
### new student in the system, including:
###   Step 1 - Login as manager/admin to obtain a JWT token
###   Step 2 - Create the academic semester (course)
###   Step 3 - Create the class (halaqa)
###   Step 4 - Register the student
###   Step 5 - Enroll the student in the class
###   Step 6 - Verify the student profile
###
### Instructions:
###   1. Run each request in order (top to bottom).
###   2. After Step 1, copy the "token" from the response and
###      set it as the value of @authToken below.
###   3. After Step 2, copy the course ID and set @courseId.
###   4. After Step 3, copy the halaqa ID and set @classId.
###   5. After Step 4, copy the student ID and set @studentId.
### =============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5107

# Update these variables after each step with real response values:
@authToken = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@semesterId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003
@courseId   = COURSE_ID_FROM_STEP_2
@classId    = CLASS_ID_FROM_STEP_3
@studentId  = STUDENT_ID_FROM_STEP_4

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 1 - Authenticate as admin/manager
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 1: Login
# Run this first. Copy the returned "token" value into @authToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Admin@1234"
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 2 - Create a Course (semester event)
# Optional: skip if a course already exists. Use its ID in Step 3.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 2: Create course
# Copy the returned "id" from the response and set it as @courseId above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventName": "Quran Memorization - Semester 1",
  "semesterId": "{{semesterId}}"
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 3 - Create a Halaqa (class)
# Optional: skip if a class already exists. Use its ID in Step 5.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 3: Create halaqa (class)
# Copy the returned "id" from the response and set it as @classId above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/halaqas
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "className": "Halaqa Al-Noor",
  "courseId": "{{courseId}}"
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 4 - Register the student
# Uses multipart/form-data (student photo is optional).
# Default login username = NationalityNumber
# Default login password = NationalityNumber
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 4: Create student
# Copy the returned "id" from the response and set it as @studentId above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/students
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----StudentBoundary

------StudentBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Name"

Yusuf Ibrahim
------StudentBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="FatherName"

Ibrahim Khalil
------StudentBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="MotherName"

Khadijah Omar
------StudentBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="NationalityNumber"

4455667788
------StudentBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="Email"

yusuf.ibrahim@example.com
------StudentBoundary--

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 5 - Enroll student in the halaqa (class)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 5: Enroll student in class
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/students/{{studentId}}/enrollments
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

"{{classId}}"

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 6 - Verify: Fetch the registered student profile
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 6: Get student profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/students/{{studentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 6b: Get student enrollments
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/students/{{studentId}}/enrollments
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 6c: Login as the newly registered student to verify credentials
# Username = NationalityNumber (4455667788)
# Password = NationalityNumber (4455667788)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "4455667788",
  "password": "4455667788"
}

###
